=== CHANGES MADE ===

== 1. crates/cli/Cargo.toml ==
Added dependencies:
- reqwest: added "stream" feature (for bytes_stream())
- chrono = { version = "0.4", features = ["serde"] }
- futures-util = "0.3"

== 2. crates/cli/src/api_client.rs ==
Changes:
a) list_workers: changed return type from Vec<WorkerSummary> to PaginatedResponse<WorkerSummary>
b) Added get_auth_status method: GET /identities/{id}/auth-status -> AuthStatus
c) Replaced patch<B, T> (returns JSON) with patch_no_content<B> (returns ()) since PATCH /identities returns 204
d) Updated set_credentials to return Result<()> instead of Result<serde_json::Value>

== 3. crates/cli/src/main.rs ==
Major changes:

a) Session start flags: Replaced single --params JSON flag with individual typed flags:
   --prompt, --n, --sentinel, --agent-cli, --model, --branch-mode, --retain-forever
   Added parse_agent_cli() and parse_branch_mode() helper functions.
   SessionParams is built from individual flags (only created if any flag is set).

b) Session list: Now prints formatted table with headers (SESSION_ID, WORKFLOW, STATUS, REPO, CREATED)

c) Session show: Enhanced output with:
   - retain_forever display
   - Session parameters detail (prompt, n, sentinel, agent_cli, model, branch_mode)
   - Jobs table with headers (JOB_ID, STATUS, CREATED, PR URL)
   - Error messages for failed jobs

d) Session delete: Added --force flag. Without --force, prompts "Delete session {id}? [y/N]"

e) Attach command: Full SSE implementation:
   - Verifies session exists and checks status (exits early for terminal states)
   - Spawns two concurrent SSE streams via tokio::spawn:
     1. Log stream: GET /sessions/:id/logs/stream -> prints "[HH:MM:SS] [LEVEL] message"
     2. Event stream: GET /sessions/:id/events -> prints "[event] Session {id}: {event}"
   - For chat sessions (WorkflowType::Chat): spawns stdin reader that sends input via POST /sessions/:id/input
   - Uses tokio::select! to run all streams concurrently

f) Logs tail: Two-phase implementation:
   - Phase 1: Fetch historical logs via GET /sessions/:id/logs (with job_id, level, last filters)
   - Phase 2: Open SSE stream to /sessions/:id/logs/stream with same filters
   - Deduplication: tracks last timestamp from history, skips SSE entries with timestamp <= last_ts
   - Also handles "session_event" SSE events for terminal state notification

g) Logs delete: Added --force flag with confirmation prompt

h) Workers list: Updated to use PaginatedResponse, prints table with headers (WORKER_ID, HOST, PLATFORM, STATUS, LAST_SEEN)

i) Credentials show: Enhanced with auth-status call:
   - Shows IdentityStatus (has_git_token, has_agent_token)
   - Calls get_auth_status and displays: git_token_status, provider, expires_at, message
   - Silently ignores auth-status errors (endpoint may not be available)
   - Default identity_id changed to "default"

j) Credentials set: Default identity_id changed to "default"

k) API key list: Prints formatted table with headers (ID, LABEL, CREATED)

l) Added helper functions:
   - print_log_entry(): formatted log output
   - truncate_str(): truncates strings with "..." for table display
   - confirm_action(): reads y/N from stdin
   - parse_agent_cli(): parses "claude_code"/"claude-code"/"cursor"
   - parse_branch_mode(): parses "main"/"pr"

m) Added SSE streaming infrastructure:
   - SessionEvent struct for deserializing session events
   - stream_sse() async function: generic SSE client that:
     - Connects with Authorization header and Accept: text/event-stream
     - Parses SSE protocol (event:, data:, comments, empty line dispatching)
     - Calls handler callback for each complete event
     - Uses futures_util::StreamExt for bytes_stream()

